There ya go....  And that is why I am broke. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ualferogue.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Alfe Rogue</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/7/02 2:18:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10167.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: erm...</span><hr size=1> hmmm last time I checked this was a rogue board, you dont see me on a monk board posting crap do you? thx la~ <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uphantazia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Phantazia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/7/02 2:22:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10167.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: erm...</span><hr size=1> It's called supply and demand which isn't a hard concept to grasp. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/unaathankaine.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Naathan Kaine</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://members.tripod.com/~Mystiqal/newanim/cosmic/dancingteke.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/7/02 2:51:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10167.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: erm...</span><hr size=1> Made a good ammount of money just being a trader in EC. I run accross all sorts of crap along the way. Get lucky once in a while in others. But most it comes from having a good ear tuned to what things sell for and the demand supply of certain items and that will help you a long way in making large ammunts of money. Also helps having a second comp with a ec toon sittiting there getting all the aucs scrolling while youre on the main comp and in a raid or xp group. Pick up supply/demand trends that way. Managed to buy IGS/Fungi/manastone/ESbp, ES legs and a crap load of other things by just knowing the trade skill. <br>
<br>
But on the other hand, i wind up giving sooo much away to guildies or random noobies in lowbie zones if i happen to be carrying something its almost funny. Once im broke, I usually start hoarding once again and reselling/trading for items I can either resell for a better rate without too much trouble or straight up cash. Trading for items can be tricky and its easy to get stuck with crap noone uses. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ularcenmistwalker.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Larcen Mistwalker</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/7/02 3:39:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10167.topic&index=21>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: erm...</span><hr size=1> This won't give you 60kpp either, but is also a good way to make money at the low levels.  All you need is a rogue with a hide/sneak skill ( sometimes takes until level 4 for some races ).  Kill bears and get a HQ Bearskin, to sell for 30pp ( or more if you're lucky ).  Head down into lower guk and auction that you are buying FS Weapons for 2pp each.  They sell at a merchant for 4-6pp depending on weapon, faction and charisma.  Rinse and repeat, carrying as many weapons as you can and still be able to move.  Mostly though I wouldn't worry about money.  I've never had more that 10kpp at a time, and I can still contribute greatly to groups and raids.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uangelsyn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Angelsyn</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://members.aol.com/tdlutenatenjou/icon_keyne.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/7/02 3:50:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10167.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: erm...</span><hr size=1> Fine, you want a relevant example?<br>
<br>
Just today I was told that I (as a Paladin) shouldn't try buying or getting a Centi Longsword... because classes that can Dual Wield will do more damage with them.<br>
<br>
So if my Paladin goes on a camp for a Lammy... or even worse, my Cleric gets invited to an area that has great drops for Melee weapons... I should just sit there and be quiet.  I don't <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> deserve</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> to roll on items that I could sell to buy the items I need.<br>
<br>
Oh, and another thing...  When you pull the NBG card, do you <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> ever</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> offer to random off the item you're replacing?  (assuming it's not a No Drop item.)<br>
<br>
If you're after a specific item, then you should get your friends to help you.  If you're in a true pick-up group, then you <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> must</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> expect that everyone will want to have the same chance to make a profit from the drops. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ualferogue.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Alfe Rogue</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/7/02 3:58:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10167.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: erm...</span><hr size=1> wow Angelsyn I never even thought about rolling on the item they are replacing, that is a good point you make i will have to bring that up next time someone raises the NBG card thx =) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uxren.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xren</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/7/02 4:21:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10167.topic&index=24>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> money</span><hr size=1> Best way to make money in the game is NOT from overpopulated dungeons like Seb/KC ect. <br>
<br>
To make a lot of money fast, first you need a group of players with actual skill. This allows you to accomplish things with less people than others, hence more loot for each person. Pickup groups simply don't work for this.<br>
<br>
Now, goto a dungeon or a zone that either is not overpopulated, OR go deep into that zone where no one but guilds go. For instance, a group of 6 of us would camp/farm the velks castle right after the zone was upgraded. Farming barbed ringmail / blood-runed armor when there were only a couple of pieces in existance gave us all a lot of cash. I scored the first pair of blood runed legs after the upgrade... after a bit of asking around, i got a total of 225k for them. The rest of the people in the group eventually got a few pieces each, and the total amount of plat made per person evened out.<br>
<br>
After that we moved on to HoT, still with the 6 man group. We all got full suits of armor, and stayed around to aqquire more which we sold off for yet more plat.<br>
<br>
Summary : the trick of making a lot of plat from non-trading is to go places normal pickup groups can't go. You'll get the items that are more rare, and hence sell for more plat.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uangelsyn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Angelsyn</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://members.aol.com/tdlutenatenjou/icon_keyne.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/7/02 6:43:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10167.topic&index=25>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: erm...</span><hr size=1> Actually, I almost always do that.<br>
<br>
When I was teamed up with a Ranger hunting rare stuff in Twilight Sea, we looted a Lesser Guard of Haste.  I won the roll, so I gave him my Seb Scale Mantle because it was an upgrade for him. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/upyrhos.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Pyrhos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/7/02 7:17:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10167.topic&index=26>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: erm...</span><hr size=1> I solo dragons. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ulomack.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lomack</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/8/02 1:08:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10167.topic&index=27>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: erm...</span><hr size=1> I've made quite a few k plat recently just doing faction work.  I killed the zillion goblins in Drogna necessary to get my faction from max kos to max ally with DiZok.  In the process I managed to make 5k+. Im almost positive I made more than 5k, just using that as a base number.  I never left the place to sell stuff, but I sure never left without all my packs totally filled.  I did leave to raid and xp, just did this during free time over the past few weeks. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uturlo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Turlo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User<